HEADWORD: Abased
<hw>A*based"</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*b⟦amac⟧st")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Lowered; humbled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <ety>[F.
<ets>abaiss⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>Borne lower than usual, as a
fess; also, having the ends of the wings turned downward towards the
point of the shield.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abasedly</ent>⟦br⟧
